.TH start-cli-backup-job-add 1  "add "
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-backup\-job\-add \- Add an automatic backup job
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli backup job add\fR [\fB\-\-cron\fR] [\fB\-\-timezone\fR] [\fB\-\-package\-ids\fR] [\fB\-\-exclude\-package\-ids\fR] [\fB\-\-keep\-tier\fR] [\fB\-\-service\-keep\-tier\fR] [\fB\-\-service\-latest\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-disabled\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> <\fITARGET_ID\fR> <\fIPASSWORD\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add an automatic backup job
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-cron\fR \fI<CRON>\fR [default: 0 3 * * *]
Five\-field cron schedule (minute, hour, day of month, month, weekday)
.TP
\fB\-\-timezone\fR \fI<TIMEZONE>\fR [default: UTC]
IANA timezone for the automatic backup schedule
.TP
\fB\-\-package\-ids\fR \fI<PACKAGE_IDS>\fR
Package IDs to include in the automatic backup
.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\-package\-ids\fR \fI<EXCLUDE_PACKAGE_IDS>\fR
Package IDs to exclude from current and future services
.TP
\fB\-\-keep\-tier\fR \fI<INTERVAL:COVERAGE>\fR
Retention tier INTERVAL:COVERAGE; accepts s, m, h, d, or w and may repeat
.TP
\fB\-\-service\-keep\-tier\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID=INTERVAL:COVERAGE>\fR
Per\-service tier PACKAGE_ID=INTERVAL:COVERAGE; may repeat
.TP
\fB\-\-service\-latest\-only\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID>\fR
Service package IDs that should keep only their latest checkpoint
.TP
\fB\-\-disabled\fR
Create the automatic backup job paused
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR

.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Human\-readable automatic backup job name
.TP
<\fITARGET_ID\fR>
Backup target identifier
.TP
<\fIPASSWORD\fR>
Password for backup encryption
